Name: Sarah 
Age: 32 
Gender: Female 
Occupation: Marketing Manager 
Ethnicity: African American 
Past Medical History: Asthma

Presentation of Case:
Sarah is a 32-year-old African American female who presents to the clinic with complaints of joint pain, fatigue, and skin rash for the past few months. She is a marketing manager and has been working long hours lately. She has a history of asthma but otherwise has been healthy. On examination, she has a butterfly rash on her face and joint tenderness in her hands and knees. Lab work shows positive antinuclear antibodies and anti-double-stranded DNA antibodies. A diagnosis of systemic lupus erythematosus is made, and she is started on treatment with hydroxychloroquine and nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs. She is advised to rest more and reduce her stress levels. She is scheduled for follow-up visits to monitor her disease activity and adjust her treatment as needed.

Name: Sarah Jones
Age: 32
Gender: Female
Occupation: Graphic Designer
Ethnicity: African American
Past Medical History: Asthma

Chief Complaint:
Joint pain, rashes, and fatigue.

History of Present Illness:
Sarah Jones is a 32-year-old African American graphic designer who presented to the clinic with complaints of joint pain, rashes, and fatigue. She reported that the joint pain had been present for several weeks and was affecting her ability to work. She also had a butterfly-shaped rash on her face that came and went. Sarah reported feeling tired and run down, with difficulty sleeping and a loss of appetite.

Physical Examination:
On examination, Sarah had a butterfly-shaped erythematous rash on her cheeks and nose. There were also erythematous, scaly lesions on her arms and legs. Her joints were tender and swollen, with limited range of motion. She had no lymphadenopathy.

Diagnosis:
Based on the clinical presentation and examination findings, Sarah was diagnosed with systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE).

Management:
Sarah was started on hydroxychloroquine and non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) for symptom relief. She was also referred to a rheumatologist

Name: Sarah Jones
Age: 32
Gender: Female
Occupation: Accountant
Ethnicity: African American
Past Medical History: Asthma, Hypertension, Depression

Case Presentation:

Sarah Jones is a 32-year-old African American female who presents to the clinic with complaints of joint pain and swelling, fatigue, and a rash on her face and arms. She reports that she has been feeling unwell for the past few months and has lost weight unintentionally. She has a past medical history of asthma, hypertension, and depression. She is currently taking albuterol, lisinopril, and sertraline.

On physical examination, Sarah has a butterfly rash over her cheeks and nose, joint tenderness and swelling in her hands and wrists, and oral ulcers.
